# Workflow Execution Rule

Use `.cursor/project/WORKFLOW.md` as the execution plan.

Before execution:

- Read `.cursor/project/PROJECT.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/STRUCTURE.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/TOOLING.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/RULES.md`.
- Read `.cursor/project/CODING_CONVENTIONS.md`.
- Read relevant command docs in `.cursor/core/commands/`.
- Read relevant state protocols in `.cursor/core/protocols/`.
- Read relevant agent docs in `.cursor/core/agents/`.
- Read enabled packs under `.cursor/packs/`.

Execution protocol:

1. Dry-run the workflow when requested or when risk is unclear.
2. Execute one phase at a time.
3. Respect task inputs, outputs, dependencies, and acceptance criteria.
4. Do not run two write tasks in parallel if outputs overlap.
5. Review completed work before marking tasks done.
6. Run verification commands from `TOOLING.md`.
7. Update `PROGRESS.md`.
8. Append recovery events to `EVENTS.jsonl` when orchestration starts.

Runtime files:

- `.cursor/project/PROGRESS.md`: human-readable status.
- `.cursor/project/EVENTS.jsonl`: append-only recovery journal.
- `.cursor/runtime/mailbox/`: progress messages for long-running work.
- `.cursor/runtime/heartbeat/`: liveness state.
- `.cursor/runtime/checkpoint/`: recovery notes.

Do not delete runtime recovery files while work is active or paused.

Detailed command behavior:

- Dry run: `.cursor/core/commands/dry-run.md`.
- Execute workflow: `.cursor/core/commands/orchestrate.md`.
- Resume workflow: `.cursor/core/commands/continue.md`.
- Report status: `.cursor/core/commands/status.md`.
- Pause workflow: `.cursor/core/commands/stop.md`.
- Validate phase completion: `.cursor/core/commands/validate.md`.
